data.text:
For the English footballer, see Arthur Wilkinson (footballer). For the English cricketer, see Arthur Wilkinson (cricketer).

Arthur Wilkinson (3 September 1919 â€“ 1968) was a British orchestral composer and arranger. He began composing while serving in the Royal Air Force during World War II, and made many contributions to film, stage shows and television.
